dummy_package

dummy_package.Rd

This function will create an RStudio project called `package0301` and populate it with `0105-run-birth-death.R` (now `run-birth-death.R`), and `0105-step-birth-death.R` (now `step_deterministic_birth_death.R`).

dummy_package(package_name)

Arguments

package_name

a string corresponding to the name you want to give your package; this should be your GitHub user name.
